comment: noticed more enemies came out after playing for a while. difficulty increased
didn't notice any change

Enemies seemed similar in difficulty to condition 4 so I modified my strategy slightly and it seemed to work better than before. I tried to do more running back and forth between the health pack and the grenade.
it was better
I backed into a corner and defended it so it was easier to not have zombies spawn behind you. I did better.
This felt the same as condition 4
Didn't notice anything different this time than from the last one (4)
Got used to the game.
zombi this time was appearing next to  me. since I was expecting this I performed good in the conditions.
Yes, I was feeling more confident and played better.
I experienced tiredness in my eyes

Did not notice a lot of changes between this condition, it did seem about the same difficulty with many more enemies than the others. There was sense of being overwhelmed at one point.     I didn't really change my gameplay much from the last condition, still fired the weapon a lot and used grenades.
moved around much faster, used grenades, shot more at the headcrabs.
Given more map familiarity, I located a defensible position which I think increased performance. I am not sure if I noticed what difference the condition made.
it seems get easier
my speed changes all the time, sometimes fast, sometimes slow.
My strategy was to be much more mobile and it seemed to work better. I could just run across the map, group up the zombies, grab the grenade and then blow up most of them.
I found the the zombies collected in the middle so it was better to stay away from there. I did better the second try with this strategy.
I felt this condition was the easiest, even though there were more zombies
The Speed of the character would change constantly. I think that is the only difference i noticed.
It was harder this time.
my speed was changes. mouse sensitivity probably too. it affected my movement and discomforted me. since it was uncomfortable to play in the conditions my performance was lower.
yes. after each condition my gameplay is improving
The movements were slower as I took damage from the enemies.
faster movements, more health packs, trying to keep zombies in front of me

I noticed the command prompt changing the movement speed, and initially I thought is was only decreasing so it made me want to stop moving.    When I noticed it going back up I took it as an opportunity to move around a bit.    Being the 3rd time playing the game, I found it easier to expect what could happen making it much easier to survive.    Since last game I died to my blind spot, this time I checked it every 8 seconds like a rear view check while driving to make sure I would not get flanked.

I noticed that around Round 2 or 3 that my movement speed (not aiming sensitivity, just character movement) increased dramatically. It was difficult to get used to, but ultimately it did help gameplay.
difficulty increased as level going up. make game harder.
My character felt quite sluggish and slow. Relative to the zombies. This made my previous strategy difficult to pull off as I wasn't as maneuverable.
I didn't really change my playstyle but it seemed the safe places got more overrun quicker now
The play area was small and the zombies spawned more together as the round went on, I think this made it more difficult
The zombies would change speed throughout the playthrough.
Each round took longer time to go to the next round.  I could use speed(Shift) this time better(in 3rd try).
The speed seems slower.  And I felt more used to the game.
every round the number of zombies increased
yes and the gameplay improved

The gameplay seemed normal at the begining and felt so until I died the first time where one hit killed me. I changed my style of gameplay to be more aggressive by firing the weapons more and aiming for the head. Think I performed better knowing one hit from the enemy killed me.
I started using the grenades more as more zombies were released

Now that I had noticed the command prompt last game, I was now checking it for updates to the game mechanics. I noticed that the zombie speed was being altered and assumed that I would eventually get rushed.    I feel my performance worsened given that I died. It was harder to deal with a change to the enemy's profile than one to my own.    I had quite a surprise when the speed was set to 3.33 and a guy was in my face immediately.
Felt just like Condition 1 (movement speed was normal again).
did not notice changes. but i performed better
seems like more zombies appear, and seems like they appear faster
Enemies got progressively harder and increased in number as the rounds increased. Definitely impacted my performance
I didn't change anythi8ng major. My gameplay stayed about the same.
the zombies moved slower but there also seemed to be more
Unlimited Ammo, Fairly quick respawn on consumables.
I think somehow I found the best way how to play the game.
zombies still strong and number of it increased every round
I dont think anything changed and i didnot perform better with these changes
I felt game got harder in this step.

Notices there was fog creeping in around me and had to use the flashlight a few times until I adapted to playing in the fog. Also used more ammo this round and held the trigger/mouse down longer.     Think I performed better after I died the first time knowing what it takes to die.
Ran back more, used grenades more, used healthpacks more

Familiarity with HL2 made getting accustomed easier than with a different game.    The point spawning was surprising compared to games where mobs would have an entrance like climbing over a fence. Made it so that no point was particularly defensible. I noticed my heart jump a bit when Unexpectedly hit from behind from a new spawn.

At round 3 it got foggy and then round 4 got even foggier. This made it difficult to see at long ranges, but ultimately this only was a minor hindrance to gameplay since round 3 and 4 are easy compared to round 5.
